    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-31T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="641"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d641">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2898: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-31T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1920—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>198. In view of reorganization of Ministry of Finance Lamont suggests that you
                    confer with Group representatives and with them take early means for
                    ascertaining whether the views of the new Minister of Communications are not
                    perhaps more enlightened than those of his predecessor in connection with
                    Hukuang and Tientsin-Pukow bonds.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
